.TH "update_tasks_flags" 9 "update_tasks_flags" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
update_tasks_flags \- update the spread flags of tasks in the cpuset.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" update_tasks_flags
.BI "(struct cpuset *cs "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cs" 12
the cpuset in which each task's spread flags needs to be changed
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Iterate through each task of \fIcs\fP updating its spread flags.  As this
function is called with cpuset_mutex held, cpuset membership stays
stable.
